"You already have your local keys. Now you can:\n"
"1. Close this window\n"
"2. Check 'Sign Kernel for Secure Boot (MOK)'\n"
"3. <b>Start the Installation</b>"

msgid "Step 3: Enroll Key in BIOS (Required to Boot)"
msgstr "Step 3: Enroll Key in BIOS (Required to Boot)"

msgid ""
"This step is only needed once. It is recommended to do it <b>after</b> "
"installing your first kernel:\n"
"1. Click 'Enroll Key' (enter a password)\n"
"2. <b>Restart</b> and select 'Enroll MOK' in the blue menu."
msgstr ""
"This step is only needed once. It is recommended to do it <b>after</b> "
"installing your first kernel:\n"
"1. Click 'Enroll Key' (enter a password)\n"
"2. <b>Restart</b> and select 'Enroll MOK' in the blue menu."

msgid "Step 4: Enable Secure Boot"
msgstr "Step 4: Enable Secure Boot"

